## Disclosed gap: gates 030-050 (freshness / andon-regression / output-count-regression)

`ggen-verify-pack`'s gates 030/040/050 require `[law].reflexive = true` and
query `ggenr:Sync` facts materialized by the reflexive-receipts pipeline
stage (`crates/ggen-engine/src/sync.rs`, Stage "P2"). That stage is
implemented ONLY on the `ggen_engine::config::GgenConfig` ("frontmatter")
schema dispatch branch. This repo's own `ggen.toml` is the OTHER schema
(`ggen_config::manifest::GgenManifest`, "declarative-rules" -- selected by
`has_generation_rules` because `[[generation.rules]]` is non-empty), whose
`[law]` table (`Law { rules: Vec<PathBuf> }`) has no `reflexive` field at
all. Gates 030/040/050 are therefore not wired here: they would never see a
`ggenr:Sync` fact and would silently never fire, which is worse than not
wiring them (a green gate that can never go red is not a gate). Only gates
010 (evidence present) and 020 (evidence green) are wired, both of which
depend solely on `ver:` facts this repo's schema can and does admit.
